Iranian President: If sanctions against Iran are lifted, nuclear negotiations can reach agreement -
Xinhua News Agency Tehran December 11th (reporters Gao Wancheng and Wang Shoubao) Iranian President Rohani said on the 11th in the Iranian capital of Tehran that if the United States lifts sanctions against Iran, the comprehensive agreement on Iran's nuclear issue can be reached to a "good agreement".
According to a message released on the Iranian President's website, Rohani said at a meeting with the Iranian ambassadors to the surrounding countries that Iran has proven its negotiating sincerity by submitting proposals to the other relevant parties to the Iran nuclear agreement.
If the US side makes a determined effort, "the road to reach agreement will be smooth."
The relevant parties to the Iran nuclear agreement began talks in the Austrian capital Vienna in April of this year to discuss the restoration of the US-Iran compliance issue.
The new round of talks began on November 29th in Vienna and was temporarily suspended on December 3rd and resumed on the 9th.